1
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:39,999
=The Litchi Road=

2
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:42,100
(Bloodthirsty Fleas)

3
00:01:42,100 --> 00:01:42,760
Left Chancellor.

4
00:01:43,140 --> 00:01:46,060
(March)

5
00:01:46,200 --> 00:01:48,480
Right Chancellor, you're in a good mood.

6
00:01:49,680 --> 00:01:53,480
Leyou Garden is a royal garden.

7
00:01:54,080 --> 00:01:56,120
His Majesty is busy

8
00:01:56,280 --> 00:01:57,520
and doesn't come here frequently

9
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:01,120
but you visit this place often.

10
00:02:02,133 --> 00:02:03,680
Left Chancellor, you know nothing.

11
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:08,520
To protect
His Majesty's favorite peony,

12
00:02:09,160 --> 00:02:12,200
I have to do my best

13
00:02:12,720 --> 00:02:13,840
to care for it.

14
00:02:15,080 --> 00:02:18,000
Even if I have to stay here every day,

15
00:02:19,640 --> 00:02:21,080
it is still my responsibility.

16
00:02:24,127 --> 00:02:25,629
Left Chancellor, did you come here

17
00:02:25,640 --> 00:02:27,000
just to say this?

18
00:02:30,280 --> 00:02:33,440
I came here on His Majesty's orders

19
00:02:33,960 --> 00:02:36,520
to ask for forgiveness for my crime.

20
00:02:47,911 --> 00:02:50,000
We are both officials
in the imperial court.

21
00:02:50,720 --> 00:02:54,080
Left Chancellor, why must you bow to me?

22
00:02:59,080 --> 00:03:00,160
His Majesty said

23
00:03:00,920 --> 00:03:04,680
you and I
are both pillars of the imperial court.

24
00:03:04,920 --> 00:03:06,520
We should be getting along.

25
00:03:07,720 --> 00:03:11,400
My retainer, Song Wuji, used my name

26
00:03:11,680 --> 00:03:14,400
and flaunted his authority in Lingnan.

27
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:16,520
He was arrogant, greedy,

28
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:17,760
and embezzled money.

29
00:03:18,480 --> 00:03:19,160
I heard

30
00:03:19,720 --> 00:03:21,760
the color of the blood bird's nest
he consumed

31
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:24,777
was even better than His Majesty's.

32
00:03:28,040 --> 00:03:28,800
In the end,

33
00:03:30,311 --> 00:03:34,511
I had to trouble you
to punish one of my own.

34
00:03:34,880 --> 00:03:38,080
I feel deeply guilty.

35
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:41,320
I've come in repentance

36
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:43,888
and hope you punish me for the crime of

37
00:03:43,911 --> 00:03:46,680
misjudging a person
and failing to see through his conduct.

38
00:03:46,680 --> 00:03:47,760
Left Chancellor,

39
00:03:48,920 --> 00:03:49,920
please stand.

40
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:55,080
Left Chancellor,

41
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:58,080
Song Wuji

42
00:03:59,600 --> 00:04:01,280
deserved it.

43
00:04:02,822 --> 00:04:04,644
What crimes did you commit,
Left Chancellor?

44
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:09,480
If news of what you did just now

45
00:04:09,880 --> 00:04:12,720
is spread out,

46
00:04:13,600 --> 00:04:15,622
it will be bad for you.

47
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:21,080
Everyone has ulterior motives.

48
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:25,880
If you hadn't let me experience this,

49
00:04:26,080 --> 00:04:27,520
I would not have believed

50
00:04:28,479 --> 00:04:30,679
that there was such a scheming person

51
00:04:30,760 --> 00:04:34,200
among the officials

52
00:04:34,520 --> 00:04:38,440
in the land of Tang.

53
00:04:41,912 --> 00:04:45,392
Left Chancellor, you are knowledgeable.

54
00:04:46,040 --> 00:04:48,160
I've always had a question

55
00:04:48,440 --> 00:04:50,160
to ask you.

56
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:56,400
Every flower in the Leyou Garden

57
00:04:57,160 --> 00:05:00,000
is pretty

58
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:03,120
but His Majesty

59
00:05:05,280 --> 00:05:07,640
only likes this old peony.

60
00:05:10,120 --> 00:05:12,960
If someone thinks its beauty
has overshadowed the rest of the flowers

61
00:05:13,920 --> 00:05:15,520
and hindered His Majesty's judgment

62
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:17,520
so he wants to get rid of it,

63
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:21,000
do you think

64
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:23,880
His Majesty should feel happy

65
00:05:26,520 --> 00:05:27,680
or unhappy?

66
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:34,520
I think

67
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:36,160
if flowers

68
00:05:36,644 --> 00:05:38,288
are competing against each other

69
00:05:38,320 --> 00:05:39,480
by blooming beautifully,

70
00:05:39,920 --> 00:05:41,520
there's nothing wrong with it.

71
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:43,160
However,

72
00:05:44,760 --> 00:05:46,680
if we are talking about a flea

73
00:05:47,320 --> 00:05:50,920
that sticks to Chang'an
and sucks Tang's blood,

74
00:05:51,400 --> 00:05:53,800
it will be a different story.

75
00:05:54,880 --> 00:05:59,080
After all, the land
belongs to His Majesty.

76
00:05:59,520 --> 00:06:02,320
Tang also belongs to His Majesty.

77
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:07,560
If His Majesty finds out one day,

78
00:06:08,280 --> 00:06:10,120
others won't even need to help him...

79
00:06:16,244 --> 00:06:17,080
Right Chancellor,

80
00:06:17,133 --> 00:06:19,688
you are busy with your duty.
I'm not supposed to disturb you.

81
00:06:19,760 --> 00:06:20,360
Farewell.

82
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:21,760
Farewell.

83
00:06:21,844 --> 00:06:23,311
I won't be sending you off then.

84
00:06:31,020 --> 00:06:34,020
=Episode 34=

85
00:06:34,840 --> 00:06:36,840
(Litchi Service Notice)
What is this?

86
00:06:37,533 --> 00:06:38,888
Order from the Inspector Office.

87
00:06:39,088 --> 00:06:40,244
Order from His Majesty.

88
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:42,960
The office is organizing
a Litchi banquet

89
00:06:43,111 --> 00:06:45,155
to celebrate
the Noble Consort's birthday.

90
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:46,240
This notice is posted

91
00:06:46,400 --> 00:06:48,800
to gather the people
to serve the imperial court

92
00:06:49,044 --> 00:06:51,355
and celebrate
with His Majesty and the Noble Consort.

93
00:06:51,560 --> 00:06:53,360
It is a blessing for us,
the people of Lingnan

94
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:55,680
to serve His Majesty
and the Noble Consort.

95
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:58,760
Everyone, please spare some money...

96
00:06:59,200 --> 00:07:01,120
We don't have any more money!

97
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:04,960
I beg you. Don't take anymore.

98
00:07:05,040 --> 00:07:07,866
Sir! You can't take anymore.

99
00:07:07,866 --> 00:07:08,320
Get lost!

100
00:07:08,320 --> 00:07:09,320
Spare some for us.

101
00:07:28,333 --> 00:07:29,688
Chief Scribe Zhao.

102
00:07:33,320 --> 00:07:33,880
Dear.

103
00:07:34,880 --> 00:07:36,280
Dear, someone is looking for you.

104
00:07:37,288 --> 00:07:38,955
How do you feel? Do you want to vomit?

105
00:07:39,400 --> 00:07:40,120
Chief Scribe Zhao.

106
00:07:40,222 --> 00:07:41,311
Someone is looking for you.

107
00:07:57,960 --> 00:07:59,760
Master, Chief Scribe Zhao is here.

108
00:08:05,400 --> 00:08:06,360
Master Konglang?

109
00:08:08,640 --> 00:08:09,600
Chief Scribe Zhao,

110
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:11,760
are you looking for this head ornament?

111
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:19,200
Do you know

112
00:08:19,760 --> 00:08:20,520
why Inspector Yu

113
00:08:20,560 --> 00:08:22,320
wants this head ornament so much?

114
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:25,360
I don't want to know.

115
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:28,240
I have no interest

116
00:08:29,280 --> 00:08:30,600
in Inspector Yu's past.

117
00:08:31,160 --> 00:08:31,760
Farewell.

118
00:08:32,360 --> 00:08:34,120
I want to tell you a story.

119
00:08:34,680 --> 00:08:35,240
When I'm done,

120
00:08:35,520 --> 00:08:37,360
perhaps you will change your mind.

121
00:08:40,280 --> 00:08:40,920
Back then,

122
00:08:41,040 --> 00:08:42,120
an evil child

123
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:43,280
killed a girl

124
00:08:43,360 --> 00:08:44,800
from the same village

125
00:08:45,160 --> 00:08:46,640
to snatch this head ornament from her.

126
00:08:47,244 --> 00:08:49,040
After the parents
of the evil child found out

127
00:08:49,040 --> 00:08:49,880
and punished him,

128
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:51,200
he burned his parents

129
00:08:51,240 --> 00:08:53,200
in a fire.

130
00:08:54,231 --> 00:08:55,151
When he was escaping,

131
00:08:55,320 --> 00:08:56,600
he lost the head ornament

132
00:08:57,120 --> 00:08:58,200
but he falsified

133
00:08:58,280 --> 00:08:59,320
a pitiful background

134
00:08:59,360 --> 00:09:01,280
to sneak into a rich merchant's family.

135
00:09:02,040 --> 00:09:03,320
Coincidentally,

136
00:09:04,080 --> 00:09:05,000
the rich merchant

137
00:09:05,040 --> 00:09:06,680
bought the same head ornament

138
00:09:06,840 --> 00:09:08,320
and gave it to his daughter.

139
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:11,800
To obtain the head ornament,

140
00:09:12,240 --> 00:09:13,560
the evil child showed ingratitude

141
00:09:13,680 --> 00:09:15,080
and colluded with pirates

142
00:09:15,080 --> 00:09:16,960
to kill
the rich merchant and his family.

143
00:09:18,840 --> 00:09:19,440
In the end,

144
00:09:20,280 --> 00:09:21,240
even the pirates

145
00:09:21,280 --> 00:09:22,529
couldn't stand his cruelty.

146
00:09:22,530 --> 00:09:24,533
The girl castrated the boy
and they didn't intervene.

147
00:09:25,560 --> 00:09:26,200
That made him

148
00:09:26,720 --> 00:09:28,200
enter the palace

149
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:30,520
and become Inspector Yu.

150
00:09:31,400 --> 00:09:32,680
The pirate back then

151
00:09:33,640 --> 00:09:34,800
was He Youguang.

152
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:35,680
Master Konglang.

153
00:09:35,960 --> 00:09:37,960
This story is just a legend.

154
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:40,120
You shouldn't believe
something you hear.

155
00:09:40,960 --> 00:09:42,200
I didn't hear it.

156
00:09:43,266 --> 00:09:44,760
I experienced it.

157
00:09:47,520 --> 00:09:48,080
I am

158
00:09:49,080 --> 00:09:50,480
the rich merchant's daughter.

159
00:09:53,880 --> 00:09:55,280
Inspector Yu killed He Youguang

160
00:09:55,400 --> 00:09:56,640
with the Right Chancellor's name

161
00:09:56,680 --> 00:09:57,733
to get his own revenge.

162
00:09:57,755 --> 00:09:59,280
He would never let the Right Chancellor

163
00:09:59,320 --> 00:10:00,400
find out the whole truth.

164
00:10:01,488 --> 00:10:03,500
Chief Scribe Zhao,
as someone who knows about this,

165
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:04,360
do you think

166
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:06,720
he will intend to kill you?

167
00:10:07,920 --> 00:10:08,640
Don't forget.

168
00:10:09,080 --> 00:10:10,680
He is an evil child

169
00:10:10,760 --> 00:10:11,840
who killed his own parents.

170
00:10:24,840 --> 00:10:27,120
If you have a grudge
against Yu Cheng'en,

171
00:10:27,400 --> 00:10:29,560
why not use the opportunity to kill him

172
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:30,360
and take revenge

173
00:10:30,440 --> 00:10:31,911
when he is in Lingnan?

174
00:10:34,840 --> 00:10:36,240
I'm sure you've realized

175
00:10:36,680 --> 00:10:38,360
my true identity.

176
00:10:38,800 --> 00:10:39,880
I won't lie to you.

177
00:10:40,360 --> 00:10:41,200
I didn't kill him

178
00:10:41,422 --> 00:10:43,000
because I didn't want to raise suspicion

179
00:10:43,022 --> 00:10:44,280
and affect the plan in Chang'an.

180
00:10:44,640 --> 00:10:45,840
Moreover, I believe

181
00:10:46,280 --> 00:10:47,600
he'll get what's coming to him.

182
00:10:49,880 --> 00:10:51,800
Chief Scribe Zhao,
you have been ambitious

183
00:10:52,022 --> 00:10:53,866
but pledging your loyalty
to Inspector Yu

184
00:10:53,933 --> 00:10:55,000
isn't a wise choice.

185
00:10:55,466 --> 00:10:57,000
He is more ruthless than He Youguang.

186
00:10:57,040 --> 00:10:59,230
He is petty and vengeful,
with absolutely no principles.

187
00:10:59,440 --> 00:11:01,400
In these troubled times,

188
00:11:02,200 --> 00:11:03,480
why don't you find yourself

189
00:11:03,520 --> 00:11:04,711
a backup plan?

190
00:11:05,280 --> 00:11:07,040
I will surely
keep your whole family safe.

191
00:11:09,280 --> 00:11:09,920
Of course,

192
00:11:10,880 --> 00:11:12,560
you can also hand this head ornament

193
00:11:12,720 --> 00:11:14,360
to Inspector Yu

194
00:11:14,577 --> 00:11:16,040
and expect him to reward you.

195
00:11:22,560 --> 00:11:25,400
Since this head ornament belongs to you,

196
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:29,040
please keep it well.

197
00:11:29,600 --> 00:11:31,400
I'll pay
for all of Konglang Guild's fees.

198
00:11:31,440 --> 00:11:33,355
Forget that I'm here today.

199
00:11:33,360 --> 00:11:33,977
Farewell.

200
00:11:34,280 --> 00:11:34,800
Farewell.

201
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:48,480
Boss.

202
00:11:49,800 --> 00:11:50,120
Look.

203
00:11:50,800 --> 00:11:52,680
Do you have a jar that looks like this?

204
00:11:53,912 --> 00:11:54,832
Sorry.

205
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:57,000
I can't make this.

206
00:11:57,000 --> 00:11:57,800
I don't have this.

207
00:11:57,800 --> 00:11:58,555
No one?

208
00:11:58,680 --> 00:11:59,840
A two-layered one. You don't?

209
00:12:00,080 --> 00:12:00,600
No.

210
00:12:00,960 --> 00:12:01,560
Sorry.

211
00:12:02,177 --> 00:12:02,888
Let me ask you.

212
00:12:04,480 --> 00:12:05,640
Do you have this jar?

213
00:12:07,680 --> 00:12:09,680
Do you have this jar?

214
00:12:09,680 --> 00:12:10,400
I don't.

215
00:12:11,777 --> 00:12:13,066
Sorry about that.

216
00:12:19,120 --> 00:12:20,520
Do you have a jar like this?

217
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:21,377
A two-layered one.

218
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:22,560
I don't have it here.

219
00:12:23,640 --> 00:12:24,440
I don't think

220
00:12:24,440 --> 00:12:26,000
you can find this in all of Lingnan.

221
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:08,920
Mr. Li,

222
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:11,120
you haven't come back for days.

223
00:13:11,840 --> 00:13:13,880
Do I need to make you some food?

224
00:13:19,920 --> 00:13:20,520
Gou'er.

225
00:13:22,600 --> 00:13:23,320
Go out.

226
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:24,440
I need some time alone.

227
00:13:26,360 --> 00:13:27,920
Mr. Li, you need to eat.

228
00:13:31,640 --> 00:13:32,760
Sure. I'll eat.

229
00:13:33,640 --> 00:13:35,240
I have bamboo rice from Tong.

230
00:13:35,360 --> 00:13:36,000
Go out.

231
00:13:42,800 --> 00:13:43,720
It's not spoiled.

232
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:46,000
Mr. Li, let me heat it up for you.

233
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:49,840
Gou'er!

234
00:13:51,560 --> 00:13:52,600
What's wrong, Mr. Li?

235
00:14:07,920 --> 00:14:08,480
Wait.

236
00:14:09,880 --> 00:14:10,440
Wait a second.

237
00:14:11,711 --> 00:14:12,720
All right. Let's go.

238
00:14:15,640 --> 00:14:16,480
Be careful.

239
00:14:16,680 --> 00:14:17,355
All right.

240
00:14:20,320 --> 00:14:21,360
Thank you.

241
00:14:21,480 --> 00:14:22,160
Mr. Li.

242
00:14:23,222 --> 00:14:25,120
Here are the thickest bamboos
you asked for.

243
00:14:25,160 --> 00:14:25,960
What do you think?

244
00:14:28,520 --> 00:14:29,240
It works.

245
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:30,560
This is it.

246
00:14:30,760 --> 00:14:32,120
Why do you want these bamboos?

247
00:14:32,647 --> 00:14:33,524
To keep litchi inside.

248
00:14:34,160 --> 00:14:35,000
Keep litchi inside?

249
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:38,360
Bamboo likes humid places
and keeps moisture well.

250
00:14:38,520 --> 00:14:40,000
If these bamboos are cut into sections

251
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:41,120
and drenched in water,

252
00:14:41,440 --> 00:14:42,760
we can put litchi inside

253
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:43,720
and seal it with mud.

254
00:14:43,840 --> 00:14:45,480
It's just like a two-layered jar.

255
00:14:46,560 --> 00:14:47,520
Lan, help me out.

256
00:14:47,733 --> 00:14:49,720
Cut the bamboos
according to their sections.

257
00:14:49,800 --> 00:14:50,320
Come on.

258
00:14:50,520 --> 00:14:51,160
Help me.

259
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:51,911
All right.

260
00:14:51,933 --> 00:14:54,270
(Inspector's Office)
Three baskets of vegetables and fruits.

261
00:14:54,360 --> 00:14:55,240
Two pots.

262
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:57,000
Three golden teeth.

263
00:14:59,320 --> 00:15:00,640
A set of toiletries.

264
00:15:01,280 --> 00:15:02,680
Lingnan is humid and hot.

265
00:15:02,720 --> 00:15:05,040
We don't have many supplies usually.

266
00:15:05,440 --> 00:15:07,240
Right now, we've even moved

267
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:08,520
the government supplies here

268
00:15:08,711 --> 00:15:10,377
including disaster relief food supplies.

269
00:15:10,880 --> 00:15:13,640
We've gathered 52 horses,

270
00:15:13,960 --> 00:15:16,000
625 stones of food,

271
00:15:16,466 --> 00:15:18,520
and we are still counting
the rest of the wares.

272
00:15:19,960 --> 00:15:20,680
This is

273
00:15:20,880 --> 00:15:22,640
a new request
sent by the Right Chancellor.

274
00:15:22,720 --> 00:15:25,240
30 additional clumps
of litchis are added.

275
00:15:25,520 --> 00:15:26,488
Should we follow it?

276
00:15:27,400 --> 00:15:29,840
I will do this myself.

277
00:15:45,280 --> 00:15:46,840
(Li Shande.)

278
00:15:46,840 --> 00:15:50,400
(I'm leaving Lingnan
and returning to the sea.)

279
00:15:50,400 --> 00:15:52,080
(My father wanted to come ashore)

280
00:15:52,080 --> 00:15:54,640
(but when I got ashore, I realized)

281
00:15:54,640 --> 00:15:58,360
(the waves on the shore
were worse than the ones at sea.)

282
00:15:59,360 --> 00:16:01,160
(My father was righteous
his whole life.)

283
00:16:01,160 --> 00:16:04,000
(In the end, he owed the people of Lingnan
because of the Sea Sail Fund.)

284
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:06,920
